      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IDEN OLIVER (6) was responsible for a very good effort last time over 1609m at this track, finishing second and just a head from the winner. Leading hope based on that recent effort. KENYA NZ (10) drew wide last start and was easily accounted for, beaten 30 metres into ninth at Launceston over 2200m. Draws out a little on the second line and may need luck at some point. Tackles a similar assignment and he can finish a lot closer this time. TOP GUN TED (4) is capable of better after finishing well back when resuming over 2200m at Launceston five days ago. Will be better for that hit-out. SWEET DIXIE (1) showed pleasing improvement last time out when third over 1609m at this course. A must for the multiples.",
